Converts a `T` into an `Arc<T>`

The conversion moves the value into a
newly allocated `Arc`. It is equivalent to
calling `Arc::new(t)`.

# Example
```rust
# use std::sync::Arc;
let x = 5;
let arc = Arc::new(5);

assert_eq!(Arc::from(x), arc);
```
